sys.path.append(path)

# Call the function of statistical bias correction from 'function_bias_correction.py'
from functions_bias_correction import  eqm, scaling

Data set up and run bias corerction for historical period¶

In this step, we establish the statistical relationship between the observations and the climate model during the historical period. The climate model output in the historical period is then bias-corrected to evaluate the effectiveness of the bias correction process.¶

In [4]:
o = historical['prism'] # Observation
p = historical['gcm']   # GCM model output (Historical)
s = p # New data to be bias-corrected
In [5]:
# Run 'scaling' method
s_bc_scaling = scaling(o, p, s, scaling_type ="multiplicative")
In [6]:
# Run 'empirical quantile mapping (eqm)' method
s_bc_eqm = eqm(o, p, s, precip=True, pr_threshold=0.1, n_quantiles=None, extrapolation='constant')

res_historical = pd.DataFrame({

    'bc_scaling': s_bc_scaling,
    'bc_eqm': s_bc_eqm,
})

# Arrange x-axis for plot 
date_range_historical = pd.date_range(start='1985-01-01', end='2014-12-31', freq='D') # Daily time-series (entire years)
august_dates_historical = date_range_historical[date_range_historical.month == 8] # Daily time-series for every August
ticks = range(0, len(august_dates_historical), 155)  #set the x-ticks to display every 5 years
labels = [date.strftime('%Y') for i, date in enumerate(august_dates_historical) if i % 155 == 0]  #set the x-ticks label to display every 10 years
In [109]:
# Check results: plot time-series
plt.figure(figsize=(11, 7))

# First subplot ('scaling' output)
plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)
plt.plot(res_historical.index, res_historical['observation'], label='Observation', color=(50/255, 50/255, 50/255, 0.5))  
plt.plot(res_historical.index, res_historical['model'], label='GCM (Historical)', color=(0, 0, 1, 0.5)) 
plt.plot(res_historical.index, res_historical['bc_scaling'], label='Scaling-corrected output', color='green', linestyle=':')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Precipitation (mm)')
plt.title('Time Series in Historical Period')
plt.xticks(ticks=ticks, labels=labels)
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)

# Second subplot ('eqm' output)
plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)
plt.plot(res_historical.index, res_historical['observation'], label='Observation', color=(50/255, 50/255, 50/255, 0.5))  
plt.plot(res_historical.index, res_historical['model'], label='GCM (Historical)', color=(0, 0, 1, 0.5))
plt.plot(res_historical.index, res_historical['bc_eqm'], label='eqm-corrected output', color='red', linestyle=':')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Precipitation (mm)')
plt.title('Time Series in Historical Period')
plt.xticks(ticks=ticks, labels=labels)
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()

Data set up and run bias corerction for future period¶

Now, we can apply bias correction to the climate data for future projections (using SSP2-4.5 as an example), though you can choose outputs from different SSP scenarios.¶

In [10]:
o = historical['prism'] # Observation
p = historical['gcm']   # GCM (Historical)
s = future['ssp245']    # New data to be bias-corrected: GCM (Future)
In [11]:
s_bc_scaling_future = scaling(o, p, s, scaling_type ="multiplicative")
s_bc_eqm_future = eqm(o, p, s, precip=True, pr_threshold=0.1, n_quantiles=None, extrapolation='constant')

Check bias-corrected outputs¶

In [12]:
# Organize dataset for bias correction and bias-corrected outputs in the future period
res_future = pd.DataFrame({
    'observation': [np.nan] * len(s), 
    'model': s,
    'bc_scaling': s_bc_scaling_future,
    'bc_eqm': s_bc_eqm_future,
})
In [13]:
# Organize dataset for bias correction and bias-corrected output in both historical and future periods
res_all = pd.DataFrame({
    'observation': o, 
    'model_historical': p,
    'model_future': pd.concat([pd.Series([np.nan] * len(historical['gcm'])), future['ssp245']], ignore_index=True),
    'bc_scaling': pd.concat([pd.Series([np.nan] * len(res_historical['bc_scaling'])), res_future['bc_scaling']], ignore_index=True),
    'bc_eqm': pd.concat([pd.Series([np.nan] * len(res_historical['bc_eqm'])), res_future['bc_eqm']], ignore_index=True),
})
